participating-org.narrative:
Tedhelte "between local language help" is a non-governmental, non-profit, democratic, apolitical and non-denominational non-governmental organization. It was created with the aim of strengthening the capacities of the Nigerien populations, particularly women and youth, so that they have a meeting place and exchanges to improve their living conditions. The main mission of the NGO is to effectively mobilize and help women and youth to take charge of their environment through sustainable development initiatives. The general objective of the NGO is to support Niger's sectoral policy objectives in meeting basic human needs, mainly in the areas of the promotion of women's rights and youth, child protection , promote access to health care, food, water, basic education, combat STI / HIV /AIDS and protect the environment.
The specific objectives of the NGO are:
Reduce the vulnerability of women and youth to create frameworks for cultural dialogue and exchange;
Support government actions in the field of education and environmental protection;
To develop the spirit of cultural mixing of solidarity and tolerance
Promote the socio-occupational integration of young people by creating jobs;
Promote the formation of a new generation of farmers and ranchers able to stabilize farms for greater productivity of laborand soil.
The NGO wants to wait for the following results:
Ensure the development and economic independence of women and youth in rural and urban areas;
Consciousness of the population for a better protection of the environment;
Ensure effective awareness of the dangers of STIs / HIV / AIDS
